\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. E. lusitanica} Samp.,{\i  Ann. Sci. Acad. Polyt. Porto}{\b  14}: 161 (1921). Very dwarf, greyish-tomentose. Rosette-leaves 15-18 × 7-8 mm, broadly obovate-spathulate, rounded at apex, mucronate or emarginate, patent, much longer than the cluster. Cluster of capitula 8-16 mm wide, compact; individual capitula 4-5 mm, not distinct. Involucral bracts c. 4 mm, obovate, stramineous, hairy, with a green spot on the back below the apex, cuspidate, with arista 1·5-2 mm. Achenes c. 1 mm, patent-villous, brown. {\i S. Spain, S.E. Portugal.} Hs Lu.
