\pard\f0\fs28 Lanate annuals. Leaves alternate, narrowed to the apex. Capitula 2-3, aggregated in terminal or axillary clusters, subglobose. Receptacle cylindrical. Bracts in 2(-3) rows, the outer small, the inner saccate, strongly compressed laterally, densely patent-lanate, coriaceous in fruit, each enclosing one female floret and falling together with the achene. Female florets with a filiform, 2-dentate corolla attached laterally to the ovary; inner florets sterile, with 5-dentate, broadly tubular corolla. Achenes obovoid, compressed; pappus absent.
